    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Weapon (any sword), Legendary (requires attunement by a Creature of the Weapon's Choice)</em></p><p><strong>Runic Bonus.</strong> You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p><p><strong>Warden’s Resolve.</strong> While attuned to this weapon, you have Immunity to the Charmed and Frightened conditions.</p><p><strong>Dragon’s Bane.</strong> When you hit a Dragon with an attack roll using this weapon, the target takes an extra 3d6 Force damage.</p><p><strong>Shadow of Ethvarn.</strong> You can take a Magic action to conjure a spectral entity in an unoccupied space within 120 feet of you. It uses the Shadow stat block with the following changes:</p><p>Its creature type is Fey.</p><p>Its alignment is Neutral.</p><p>It cannot create new shadows.</p><p>It remains until it drops to 0 Hit Points or you dismiss it as a Magic action. You control this entity, deciding how it acts and moves.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
